# Web Frontend

The dashboard is vanilla JS + HTML served by `server.py` on port 8787. No build step, no framework.

## Architecture

- `web/index.html` — single-page layout
- `web/app.js` — all client logic, fetches from `server.py` API endpoints
- `server.py` — Python HTTP server, serves static files from `web/` and JSON API endpoints

## Conventions

- All API calls go to `http://127.0.0.1:8787/...`
- Keep it simple: no npm, no bundler, no TypeScript
- Server must be started with admin elevation if stats.nba.com calls are needed (WinError 10013)

## Starting the server

```powershell
powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File ".\run_ui.ps1" -OddsApiKey "KEY"
```

Or directly:

```powershell
.\.venv\Scripts\python.exe server.py
```
